==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wapiti
<hw>Wap"i*ti</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably the
Iroquois name. <ets>Bartlett</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
American elk (<spn>Cervus Canadensis</spn>). It is closely related to
the European red deer, which it somewhat exceeds in size.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ By some writers it is thought to be a variety of the red
deer, but it is considered a distinct species by others. It is noted for
the large, branching antlers of the male.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wapp</ent>⟦br⟧
